<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,259,2014]" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,367,403,429]" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Mature larva.</emphasis>
Length: body 8.5–9.0 mm; antennae 
<quantity box="[796,936,403,430]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.35" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="3.2" pageId="5" pageNumber="61" unit="mm" value="3.35" valueMax="3.5" valueMin="3.2">3.2–3.5 mm</quantity>
; cerci 6.5–7.0 mm; paracercus 
<quantity box="[1293,1433,403,430]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.35" metricValueMax="7.5" metricValueMin="7.2" pageId="5" pageNumber="61" unit="mm" value="7.35" valueMax="7.5" valueMin="7.2">7.2–7.5 mm</quantity>
. General coloration dark brownish yellow (
<figureCitation box="[627,710,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–22" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,213,1913]" captionTargetId="figure-19@6.[164,1423,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17–22. Larva of Edmundsula meghamalaiensis n. sp. 17. Dorsal view; 18. Labrum; 19. Labrum dorsal view; 20. Hypopharynx; 21. Left mandible; 22. Right mandible." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5763337" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5763337/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,259,2014]" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,270,475,501]" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Head.</emphasis>
Dark brown, washed with pale yellow. Upper portion of male compound eye reddish, lower portion black. Antennae white. Labrum (
<figureCitation box="[519,650,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–22" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,213,1913]" captionTargetId="figure-19@6.[164,1423,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17–22. Larva of Edmundsula meghamalaiensis n. sp. 17. Dorsal view; 18. Labrum; 19. Labrum dorsal view; 20. Hypopharynx; 21. Left mandible; 22. Right mandible." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5763337" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5763337/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Figs 18–19</figureCitation>
): dorsum with two rows of thin, long setae; anterior region with a row of feather like setae ventrally; anteromedian emargination with moderate ‘V’ shaped cleft and without denticles. Hypopharynx (
<figureCitation box="[320,405,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–22" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,213,1913]" captionTargetId="figure-19@6.[164,1423,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17–22. Larva of Edmundsula meghamalaiensis n. sp. 17. Dorsal view; 18. Labrum; 19. Labrum dorsal view; 20. Hypopharynx; 21. Left mandible; 22. Right mandible." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5763337" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5763337/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
): lingua with well developed lateral process; anterior margin deeply cleft; superlingua with a row of setae on anterior margin. Mandibles: (
<figureCitation box="[659,788,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–22" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,213,1913]" captionTargetId="figure-19@6.[164,1423,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17–22. Larva of Edmundsula meghamalaiensis n. sp. 17. Dorsal view; 18. Labrum; 19. Labrum dorsal view; 20. Hypopharynx; 21. Left mandible; 22. Right mandible." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5763337" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5763337/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Figs 21–22</figureCitation>
) translucent, with dark brown incisors and molars; lateral margins with scattered setae, inner incisor slightly longer than outer one. Maxilla (
<figureCitation box="[1081,1166,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–31" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,182,1894]" captionTargetId="figure-23@7.[151,1436,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 23–31. Larva of Edmundsula meghamalaiensis n. sp. 23. Maxilla; 24. Labium; 25. Glossae dorsal view; 26. Foreleg; 27. Midleg; 28. Hindleg; 29. Hind femur anterior margin; 30. Hind tibia; 31. Claw." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5763341" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5763341/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
): segments I– 
<collectionCode box="[1322,1350,656,682]" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">III</collectionCode>
of palp equal in length, apical segment not tapering at apex. Labium (
<figureCitation box="[841,972,691,718]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–31" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,182,1894]" captionTargetId="figure-23@7.[151,1436,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 23–31. Larva of Edmundsula meghamalaiensis n. sp. 23. Maxilla; 24. Labium; 25. Glossae dorsal view; 26. Foreleg; 27. Midleg; 28. Hindleg; 29. Hind femur anterior margin; 30. Hind tibia; 31. Claw." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5763341" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5763341/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Figs 24–25</figureCitation>
): palps 3-segmented, segments 
<collectionCode box="[1324,1342,692,718]" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">II</collectionCode>
– 
<collectionCode box="[1357,1385,692,718]" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">III</collectionCode>
narrower, with row of thick setae on dorsal margin of third segment; outer and inner margins of palp with row of long and pointed setae; segment I slightly longer than segment 
<collectionCode box="[802,823,764,790]" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">II</collectionCode>
, segment 
<collectionCode box="[935,963,764,790]" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">III</collectionCode>
shorter than segment 
<collectionCode box="[1210,1231,764,790]" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">II</collectionCode>
, tapering at apex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,259,2014]" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,799,825]" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Thorax.</emphasis>
Pale yellowish brown, irregularly washed with dark brown; pronotum with lateral margins white; dark brownish with diffuse hypodermal markings. Legs: brownish yellow; coxae brown; outer surface of all femora with long, thick and thin setae; dorsal surface of foreleg with short stout setae as a group in the distal region; pale macula on distal end (
<figureCitation box="[314,400,907,934]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–31" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,182,1894]" captionTargetId="figure-23@7.[151,1436,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 23–31. Larva of Edmundsula meghamalaiensis n. sp. 23. Maxilla; 24. Labium; 25. Glossae dorsal view; 26. Foreleg; 27. Midleg; 28. Hindleg; 29. Hind femur anterior margin; 30. Hind tibia; 31. Claw." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5763341" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5763341/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
); femur of midleg moderately developed with numerous short stout setae on dorsal surface (
<figureCitation box="[160,244,943,969]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–31" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,182,1894]" captionTargetId="figure-23@7.[151,1436,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 23–31. Larva of Edmundsula meghamalaiensis n. sp. 23. Maxilla; 24. Labium; 25. Glossae dorsal view; 26. Foreleg; 27. Midleg; 28. Hindleg; 29. Hind femur anterior margin; 30. Hind tibia; 31. Claw." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5763341" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5763341/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
); dorsal surface of hindfemora with numerous short stout setae (
<figureCitation box="[961,1093,943,969]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–31" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,182,1894]" captionTargetId="figure-23@7.[151,1436,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 23–31. Larva of Edmundsula meghamalaiensis n. sp. 23. Maxilla; 24. Labium; 25. Glossae dorsal view; 26. Foreleg; 27. Midleg; 28. Hindleg; 29. Hind femur anterior margin; 30. Hind tibia; 31. Claw." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5763341" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5763341/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Figs 28–29</figureCitation>
). Fore and mid tibia with thick feathered setae and long stout setae; hind tibia with thick feathered setae (
<figureCitation box="[988,1073,979,1005]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–31" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,182,1894]" captionTargetId="figure-23@7.[151,1436,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 23–31. Larva of Edmundsula meghamalaiensis n. sp. 23. Maxilla; 24. Labium; 25. Glossae dorsal view; 26. Foreleg; 27. Midleg; 28. Hindleg; 29. Hind femur anterior margin; 30. Hind tibia; 31. Claw." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5763341" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5763341/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
). Claws with denticles, progressively larger from the middle, apical denticle much larger (
<figureCitation box="[810,893,1015,1041]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–31" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,182,1894]" captionTargetId="figure-23@7.[151,1436,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 23–31. Larva of Edmundsula meghamalaiensis n. sp. 23. Maxilla; 24. Labium; 25. Glossae dorsal view; 26. Foreleg; 27. Midleg; 28. Hindleg; 29. Hind femur anterior margin; 30. Hind tibia; 31. Claw." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5763341" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5763341/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,259,2014]" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,323,1051,1077]" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Terga I–X dark yellowish brown with diffuse hypodermal markings; terga I– 
<collectionCode box="[1227,1256,1052,1078]" country="Norway" name="Mykotektet, National Veterinary Institute" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">VI</collectionCode>
with yellowish streaks laterally; terga IV–IX with posteriolateral spines, progressively larger posteriorly, spines on terga VII–IX pointed (
<figureCitation box="[251,336,1123,1150]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–37" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1328,1352]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,182,1294]" captionTargetId="figure-19@8.[151,1436,181,1304]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 32–37. Larva of Edmundsula meghamalaiensis n. sp. 32. Gill I; 33. Gill III; 34. Gill V; 35. Gill VII; 36. Subanal plate ♂ (Arrow indicate genital parts); 37. Subanal palte ♀." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5763343" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5763343/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
). Gills on segments I–VII; gill I slender and lanceolate with branched tracheae; dorsal and ventral portions of lamellae of gills 
<collectionCode box="[477,495,1160,1186]" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">II</collectionCode>
–VII wider, long and smoothly tapered at apex (
<figureCitation box="[1046,1179,1159,1186]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–37" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1328,1352]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,182,1294]" captionTargetId="figure-19@8.[151,1436,181,1304]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 32–37. Larva of Edmundsula meghamalaiensis n. sp. 32. Gill I; 33. Gill III; 34. Gill V; 35. Gill VII; 36. Subanal plate ♂ (Arrow indicate genital parts); 37. Subanal palte ♀." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5763343" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5763343/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Figs 32–35</figureCitation>
). Subanal plate deeply cleft in male and female larva (
<figureCitation box="[504,636,1195,1222]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–37" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1328,1352]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,182,1294]" captionTargetId="figure-19@8.[151,1436,181,1304]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 32–37. Larva of Edmundsula meghamalaiensis n. sp. 32. Gill I; 33. Gill III; 34. Gill V; 35. Gill VII; 36. Subanal plate ♂ (Arrow indicate genital parts); 37. Subanal palte ♀." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5763343" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5763343/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Figs 36–37</figureCitation>
). Paracercus longer than cerci; caudal filaments with whorl of setae on alternate segments, setae shorter than length of corresponding segment.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,259,2014]" box="[199,400,1267,1293]" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,275,1267,1293]" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Adult.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="61" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,259,2014]" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1303,1329]" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Etymology.</emphasis>
