).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="61" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,259,2014]" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1411,1437]" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Vasanth &amp; Subramanian &amp; Selvakumar &amp; Kubendran &amp; Sivaramakrishnan, 2021" authorityName="Vasanth &amp; Subramanian &amp; Selvakumar &amp; Kubendran &amp; Sivaramakrishnan" authorityYear="2021" box="[330,673,1411,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Leptophlebiidae" genus="Edmundsula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="meghamalaiensis" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[330,673,1411,1437]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Edmundsula meghamalaiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[683,747,1411,1437]" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[683,747,1411,1437]" pageId="5" pageNumber="61" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be distinguished from the previously described species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Sivaramakrishnan 1985" authorityName="Sivaramakrishnan" authorityYear="1985" box="[151,519,1447,1474]" class="Insecta" family="Leptophlebiidae" genus="Edmundsula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lotica">
<emphasis box="[151,246,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">E. lotica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sivaramakrishnan, K. G." box="[253,519,1447,1474]" pageId="5" pageNumber="61" pagination="235 - 239" refId="ref5772" refString="Sivaramakrishnan, K. G. (1985) New genus and species of Atalophlebiinae (Ephemeroptera: Leptophlebiidae) from southern India. Annals Entomological Society of America, 78, 235 - 239." type="journal article" year="1985">Sivaramakrishnan 1985</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by the following combination of larval characters: (i) anteromedian emargination of labrum with moderate ‘V’ shaped cleft and without denticles (
<figureCitation box="[879,1010,1483,1509]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–22" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,213,1913]" captionTargetId="figure-19@6.[164,1423,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17–22. Larva of Edmundsula meghamalaiensis n. sp. 17. Dorsal view; 18. Labrum; 19. Labrum dorsal view; 20. Hypopharynx; 21. Left mandible; 22. Right mandible." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5763337" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5763337/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Figs 18–19</figureCitation>
); (ii) segment I–III of maxillary palps shorter and apical segment not tapering at apex (
<figureCitation box="[691,773,1519,1545]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–31" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,182,1894]" captionTargetId="figure-23@7.[151,1436,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 23–31. Larva of Edmundsula meghamalaiensis n. sp. 23. Maxilla; 24. Labium; 25. Glossae dorsal view; 26. Foreleg; 27. Midleg; 28. Hindleg; 29. Hind femur anterior margin; 30. Hind tibia; 31. Claw." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5763341" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5763341/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
); (iii) segment II–III of labial palp narrower and with a row of thick setae on the dorsal margin of third segment (
<figureCitation box="[745,877,1555,1582]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–31" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,182,1894]" captionTargetId="figure-23@7.[151,1436,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 23–31. Larva of Edmundsula meghamalaiensis n. sp. 23. Maxilla; 24. Labium; 25. Glossae dorsal view; 26. Foreleg; 27. Midleg; 28. Hindleg; 29. Hind femur anterior margin; 30. Hind tibia; 31. Claw." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5763341" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5763341/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Figs 24–25</figureCitation>
); (iv) distal region of dorsal surface of the foreleg with a group of short spines (
<figureCitation box="[478,563,1591,1618]" captionStart="FIGURES 23–31" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,182,1894]" captionTargetId="figure-23@7.[151,1436,181,1894]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 23–31. Larva of Edmundsula meghamalaiensis n. sp. 23. Maxilla; 24. Labium; 25. Glossae dorsal view; 26. Foreleg; 27. Midleg; 28. Hindleg; 29. Hind femur anterior margin; 30. Hind tibia; 31. Claw." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5763341" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5763341/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,259,2014]" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,1627,1653]" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Habitat:</emphasis>
Larvae of 
<taxonomicName authority="Vasanth &amp; Subramanian &amp; Selvakumar &amp; Kubendran &amp; Sivaramakrishnan, 2021" authorityName="Vasanth &amp; Subramanian &amp; Selvakumar &amp; Kubendran &amp; Sivaramakrishnan" authorityYear="2021" box="[419,760,1627,1653]" class="Insecta" family="Leptophlebiidae" genus="Edmundsula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="meghamalaiensis" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[419,760,1627,1653]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Edmundsula meghamalaiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[766,828,1627,1653]" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[766,828,1627,1653]" pageId="5" pageNumber="61" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
inhabit first order (from 
<quantity box="[1104,1174,1627,1654]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="61" unit="m" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3 m</quantity>
wide) mountain stream (Manalar stream, 
<quantity box="[345,432,1663,1690]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.53" pageId="5" pageNumber="61" unit="m" value="1530.0">1530 m</quantity>
a.s.l.) of the Meghamalai Wildlife Sanctuary, Theni District, 
<collectingRegion box="[1139,1274,1663,1689]" country="India" name="Tamil Nadu" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Tamil Nadu</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation box="[1291,1425,1663,1690]" captionStart="FIGURES 57–60" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1042,1066]" captionTargetBox="[177,1411,182,1018]" captionTargetId="figure-23@13.[177,1411,181,1018]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 57–60. Type locality of new species. 57. Choroterpes (C.) andamanensis n. sp.; 58–59. Edmundsula meghamalaiensis n. sp.; 60. Megaglena agasthiya n. sp." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5763351" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5763351/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Figs 58–59</figureCitation>
). The stream is characterized by medium water temperature (18–22°С at the time of sampling) and average current velocity. Larvae were collected from cobbles and pebbles where the new species was found with the larvae of the 
<taxonomicName box="[192,303,1772,1798]" class="Insecta" family="Baetidae" genus="Baetis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[192,262,1772,1797]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Baetis</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[315,468,1771,1798]" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Afronurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[315,428,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Afronurus</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[481,659,1771,1798]" class="Insecta" family="Leptophlebiidae" genus="Choroterpes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[481,620,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Choroterpes</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[713,878,1771,1798]" class="Insecta" family="Teloganodidae" genus="Dudgeodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[713,839,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Dudgeodes</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="64" pageId="5" pageNumber="61" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,259,2014]" lastBlockId="8.[151,1437,1434,1643]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="64" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1807,1833]" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Discussion:</emphasis>
With an array of several plesiomorphic character states, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sivaramakrishnan" authorityYear="1985" box="[989,1129,1807,1833]" class="Insecta" family="Leptophlebiidae" genus="Edmundsula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[989,1129,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Edmundsula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a genus of Gondwanian origin, presently the genus is endemic to southern peninsular 
<collectingCountry box="[834,894,1843,1869]" name="India" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">India</collectingCountry>
, which may have phylogenetic links with genera disjunctly distributed in 
<collectingCountry box="[426,539,1879,1905]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[551,688,1879,1905]" name="Madagascar" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[700,843,1879,1905]" name="South Africa" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">South Africa</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[897,1003,1879,1905]" name="Australia" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Australia</collectingCountry>
. However, this requires in depth study through further exploration in respective areas. Furthermore, 
<bibRefCitation author="Sivaramakrishnan, K. G." box="[839,1123,1915,1942]" pageId="5" pageNumber="61" pagination="235 - 239" refId="ref5772" refString="Sivaramakrishnan, K. G. (1985) New genus and species of Atalophlebiinae (Ephemeroptera: Leptophlebiidae) from southern India. Annals Entomological Society of America, 78, 235 - 239." type="journal article" year="1985">Sivaramakrishnan (1985)</bibRefCitation>
suggested a tenuous link of 
<taxonomicName authority="Sivaramakrishnan 1985" authorityName="Sivaramakrishnan" authorityYear="1985" box="[151,565,1951,1978]" class="Insecta" family="Leptophlebiidae" genus="Edmundsula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,291,1951,1977]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Edmundsula</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sivaramakrishnan, K. G." box="[299,565,1951,1978]" pageId="5" pageNumber="61" pagination="235 - 239" refId="ref5772" refString="Sivaramakrishnan, K. G. (1985) New genus and species of Atalophlebiinae (Ephemeroptera: Leptophlebiidae) from southern India. Annals Entomological Society of America, 78, 235 - 239." type="journal article" year="1985">Sivaramakrishnan 1985</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authority="Penniket 1961" authorityName="Penniket" authorityYear="1961" box="[631,954,1951,1977]" class="Insecta" family="Leptophlebiidae" genus="Neozephlebia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[631,783,1951,1977]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Neozephlebia</emphasis>
Penniket 1961
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1024,1175,1951,1978]" name="New Zealand" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
due to the dorsolateral expansion of the glossae in both the genera. Dense rows of setae on the outer margins of fore and middle legs in 
<taxonomicName authority="Sivaramakrishnan 1985" authorityName="Sivaramakrishnan" authorityYear="1985" box="[151,561,1434,1461]" class="Insecta" family="Leptophlebiidae" genus="Edmundsula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,291,1435,1461]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="64">Edmundsula</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sivaramakrishnan, K. G." box="[297,561,1434,1461]" pageId="8" pageNumber="64" pagination="235 - 239" refId="ref5772" refString="Sivaramakrishnan, K. G. (1985) New genus and species of Atalophlebiinae (Ephemeroptera: Leptophlebiidae) from southern India. Annals Entomological Society of America, 78, 235 - 239." type="journal article" year="1985">Sivaramakrishnan 1985</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and in 
<taxonomicName authority="Peters &amp; Edmunds 1970" authorityName="Peters &amp; Edmunds" authorityYear="1970" box="[640,1000,1435,1461]" class="Insecta" family="Leptophlebiidae" genus="Indialis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[640,726,1435,1461]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="64">Indialis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Peters, W. L. &amp; Edmunds, G. F. Jr." box="[731,1000,1435,1461]" pageId="8" pageNumber="64" pagination="157 - 240" refId="ref5406" refString="Peters, W. L. &amp; Edmunds, G. F. Jr. (1970) Revision of the generic classification of the Eastern Hemisphere Leptophlebiidae (Ephemeroptera). Pacific Insects, 12 (1), 157 - 240." type="journal article" year="1970">Peters &amp; Edmunds 1970</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, another genus endemic to southern 
<collectingCountry name="India" pageId="8" pageNumber="64">India</collectingCountry>
apparently show relationship established the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boonsoong &amp; Sartori" authorityYear="2016" box="[765,938,1471,1497]" class="Insecta" family="Leptophlebiidae" genus="Sangpradubina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[765,938,1471,1497]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="64">Sangpradubina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1005,1105,1471,1497]" name="Thailand" pageId="8" pageNumber="64">Thailand</collectingCountry>
as pointed out by 
<bibRefCitation author="Boonsoong, B. &amp; Sartori, M." pageId="8" pageNumber="64" pagination="587 - 599" refId="ref5048" refString="Boonsoong, B. &amp; Sartori, M. (2016) Sangpradubina, an astonishing new mayfly genus from Thailand (Ephemeroptera: Leptophlebiidae: Atalophlebiinae). Zootaxa, 4169 (3), 587 - 599. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4169.3.11" type="journal article" year="2016">Boonsoong &amp; Sartori (2016)</bibRefCitation>
; 
